    <p>The clinic has a kitch­enette and a room with a one-way mir­ror that al­lows doc­tors and par­ents to dis­creetly ob­serve a child’s in­ter­ac­tion with the ther­a­pist.</p>
    <p>A child is much more likely to be­have nat­u­rally when there is less at­ten­tion on him or her and may also re­act dif­fer­ently when away from his par­ents.</p>
    <p>The in­sights gained by the ther­a­pist from ob­serv­ing the child are use­ful in cus­tomis­ing an ef­fec­tive care plan.</p>

